history.content:
Do you aspire to be a future leader in the tech industry? At Toppa @ Berkeley, we help you unlock your full potential! Toppa is a non-profit organization funded in Google, and we are it’s first university chapter. We aim to equip the East Asian community with the technical skills and soft skills that foster career success. In addition to weekly leadership training and mentorship from Google, we are also excited to host the Google solution challenge this semester and you have the option to join our competing projects.

 

If we sound like a good fit for you, feel free to come to our info session on Feb 3rd 8-9 pm at Wheeler 222, or Feb 5th 8-9 pm (location TBD) by filling out this RSVP link.

 

Also follow us on facebook and apply through our website!

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TOPPAatBerkeley/

Website: https://toppa.berkeley.edu
history.subject: Join Toppa @ Berkeley!
